TOPIC: JAVA SUSTRING
Question: In first line user give a string and in second line user give Starting and ending index from where to where he/she will break the String and output is only those word of that string which user needs. This problem is taken in HackerRank.
Logic: User give a string that is stored in a String variable and user also give from where to where he break the string so this is int type and store a two different variable for starting index and last index. and print with the help of substring(starting index,last index).
Sample Input
Helloworld
3 7
Sample Output
lowo
SOLUTION
import java.io.*;
import java.util.*;
import java.text.*;
import java.math.*;
import java.util.regex.*;

public class Solution {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Scanner in = new Scanner(System.in);
        String S = in.next();
        int start = in.nextInt();
        int end = in.nextInt();
        System.out.println(S.substring(start, end));
    }
}
